It was only a nightmare,

554
00:34:03,954 --> 00:34:05,204
don't be afraid.

555
00:34:06,891 --> 00:34:09,768
He must be really scared all alone.

556
00:34:37,817 --> 00:34:38,690
Hello?

557
00:34:39,813 --> 00:34:41,438
Really, you've found the Devil?!

558
00:34:41,950 --> 00:34:42,654
Okay, got it!

559
00:34:43,649 --> 00:34:44,338
Mom!

560
00:34:45,082 --> 00:34:46,117
The General Manager said that he found the Devil.

561
00:34:46,117 --> 00:34:47,169
I have to go find him quickly.

562
00:34:47,430 --> 00:34:48,458
Jia Di,

563
00:34:51,334 --> 00:34:54,739
he must of had his reasons for not telling you he was sick.

564
00:34:55,053 --> 00:34:56,679
He's afraid of seeing you sad.

565
00:34:58,276 --> 00:35:00,153
I know I'll definitely be really sad, but...

566
00:35:01,709 --> 00:35:03,519
You don't understand.

567
00:35:04,316 --> 00:35:07,209
You don't know how much that kind of sadness hurts.

568
00:35:09,928 --> 00:35:11,988
When your father was sick in hospital,

569
00:35:12,195 --> 00:35:15,159
I also thought I was really strong and really brave.

570
00:35:16,251 --> 00:35:17,674
But then I realized that

571
00:35:18,035 --> 00:35:19,742
I was more and more afraid of walking into the ward.

572
00:35:20,032 --> 00:35:22,627
I was afraid of seeing him get thinner and thinner.

573
00:35:23,213 --> 00:35:24,593
Seeing him talk less and less.

574
00:35:26,455 --> 00:35:28,763
I was afraid of seeing him getting closer and closer to death.

575
00:35:28,763 --> 00:35:30,386
Getting further and further away from me.

576
00:35:31,396 --> 00:35:33,306
So I won't stop you from going to see him,

577
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:36,024
but you must be prepared.

578
00:35:36,523 --> 00:35:39,803
A person doesn't fight a disease alone,

579
00:35:40,148 --> 00:35:42,266
he does it with all those who love him.

580
00:35:44,431 --> 00:35:45,712
If you want to see him,

581
00:35:46,451 --> 00:35:47,765
you must be stronger than him.

582
00:35:49,750 --> 00:35:50,972
I will be very strong.

583
00:35:52,776 --> 00:35:53,617
Mom.

584
00:35:59,254 --> 00:36:00,318
Huo Yan.

585
00:36:05,403 --> 00:36:06,231
Yan Shu,

586
00:36:06,940 --> 00:36:09,047
when you were little, you used to help Huo Da cover up everything.

587
00:36:09,888 --> 00:36:11,005
Helping him write repentence letters.

588
00:36:11,467 --> 00:36:13,539
Pretending to be his parent and calling the school when he got in trouble.

589
00:36:14,060 --> 00:36:15,102
It's not like I didn't know.

590
00:36:16,599 --> 00:36:17,650
But this,

591
00:36:19,035 --> 00:36:20,565
how could you hide it from everyone,

592
00:36:21,564 --> 00:36:22,630
and help him lie to us?

593
00:36:24,589 --> 00:36:25,527
Don't blame Yan Shu.

594
00:36:25,923 --> 00:36:28,058
It's because of me that everyone hates her now.

595
00:36:28,499 --> 00:36:29,372
It's all my fault.

596
00:36:30,267 --> 00:36:32,434
It was me who asked her to bear these grievances.

597
00:36:34,611 --> 00:36:35,487
I'll leave now.

598
00:36:35,701 --> 00:36:36,434
You two can talk.

599
00:36:52,404 --> 00:36:55,464
You're a General Manager, but do you want to become a Private Investigator instead?

600
00:36:59,173 --> 00:37:00,153
Don't laugh.

601
00:37:02,175 --> 00:37:03,809
You mean you want me to cry?

602
00:37:05,999 --> 00:37:07,903
Hiding your disease, lying to everyone.

603
00:37:08,218 --> 00:37:09,029
Don't laugh.

604
00:37:20,467 --> 00:37:21,833
Please don't tell Jia Di.

605
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:24,215
So this is the way you protect her?

606
00:37:26,330 --> 00:37:29,466
I'm not that great, I just don't feel like...

607
00:37:29,779 --> 00:37:30,717
seeing her cry.

608
00:37:33,022 --> 00:37:34,155
Then there's no problem.

609
00:37:35,780 --> 00:37:37,000
No problem?

610
00:37:41,153 --> 00:37:41,958
She's Tong Jia Di,

611
00:37:42,673 --> 00:37:43,764
the bravest girl.

612
00:37:45,092 --> 00:37:46,193
Have you forgotten?

613
00:37:47,561 --> 00:37:50,438
The first time you met, she was willing to believe in you,

614
00:37:50,977 --> 00:37:54,353
and risked her life to help you finish that stunt.

615
00:37:56,289 --> 00:37:57,728
Don't worry about her.

616
00:37:58,103 --> 00:37:59,071
She won't cry.

617
00:38:01,164 --> 00:38:03,122
You picked an exchange coupon to give her happiness.

618
00:38:03,645 --> 00:38:05,211
You can't be so unreliable.

619
00:38:06,574 --> 00:38:07,556
Giving her happiness

620
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:09,006
is your responsibility!

621
00:38:10,522 --> 00:38:12,022
I can't give it to her.

622
00:38:12,022 --> 00:38:13,513
Even until the day I die,

623
00:38:13,513 --> 00:38:15,193
I can't make her happy.

624
00:38:15,724 --> 00:38:17,106
The one who's going to die isn't you.

625
00:38:17,336 --> 00:38:19,295
Of course you can say it so easily!

626
00:38:26,895 --> 00:38:28,932
Go give her happiness.

627
00:38:29,301 --> 00:38:30,323
Go love her.

628
00:38:31,737 --> 00:38:32,237
Go.

629
00:38:34,604 --> 00:38:36,101
I asked you to go love her.

630
00:38:36,603 --> 00:38:38,426
Don't let her go through so much pain for me.

631
00:38:39,178 --> 00:38:40,896
Listen...

632
00:38:44,513 --> 00:38:46,103
When you were cruel to her,

633
00:38:46,354 --> 00:38:47,414
she didn't give up on you.

634
00:38:47,881 --> 00:38:48,958
She still chose to believe in you.

635
00:38:49,679 --> 00:38:51,397
Where did your courage go?

636
00:38:51,665 --> 00:38:53,147
Are you the type to just give up?

637
00:38:55,166 --> 00:38:56,175
Listen to me.

638
00:38:57,344 --> 00:39:01,484
If you really love her, then for her sake, you must live on.

639
00:39:23,922 --> 00:39:24,737
Yan Shu,

640
00:39:26,573 --> 00:39:27,766
I'm sorry

641
00:39:28,473 --> 00:39:29,546
and...

642
00:39:29,798 --> 00:39:30,863
thank you.

643
00:39:33,285 --> 00:39:34,724
I was only helping Huo Da

644
00:39:35,669 --> 00:39:37,223
to get Jia Di to give up on him,

645
00:39:39,296 --> 00:39:41,642
to let him not have any last regrets,

646
00:39:42,204 --> 00:39:44,359
and willingly stay in the hospital for treatment.

647
00:39:44,797 --> 00:39:47,538
I didn't want to hide it from you and Uncle Huo.

648
00:39:49,989 --> 00:39:51,792
I'm sorry,

649
00:39:52,082 --> 00:39:53,401
I blamed you wrongly

650
00:39:54,772 --> 00:39:55,973
and said those things to you.

651
00:39:58,923 --> 00:40:03,704
All the grievances in face of death are nothing.

652
00:40:05,234 --> 00:40:07,422
I just hope that Huo Da will live.

653
00:40:08,237 --> 00:40:09,089
He definitely will.

654
00:40:09,431 --> 00:40:10,369
We have to believe.

655
00:40:12,776 --> 00:40:13,994
With you here to face it with me,

656
00:40:14,264 --> 00:40:15,237
of course I can believe.

657
00:40:17,480 --> 00:40:18,385
Actually,

658
00:40:18,604 --> 00:40:20,334
I really wanted to tell you the truth.

659
00:40:22,078 --> 00:40:27,296
Especially after seeing Jia Di waiting outside my house.

660
00:40:29,327 --> 00:40:31,547
Jia Di already knows about Huo Da's illness.

661
00:40:50,791 --> 00:40:53,595
A person doesn't fight a disease alone,

662
00:40:53,980 --> 00:40:56,442
he does it with all those who love him.

663
00:40:56,910 --> 00:40:57,982
If you want to see him,

664
00:40:58,910 --> 00:41:00,253
you must be stronger than him.

665
00:41:53,827 --> 00:42:01,232
I'm so happy that God gave me this chance to let me have what I wanted.

666
00:42:06,348 --> 00:42:08,043
I didn't want to leave you with pain.

667
00:42:08,476 --> 00:42:10,264
What right do you have to make that decision by yourself?

668
00:42:12,044 --> 00:42:13,953
It was you who barged into my circle.

669
00:42:15,847 --> 00:42:17,859
I always let you do what you wanted,

670
00:42:18,239 --> 00:42:20,053
but only this time I won't let you.

671
00:42:21,865 --> 00:42:23,021
I'm probably going to die.

672
00:42:24,396 --> 00:42:25,631
You don't have to die.

673
00:42:28,110 --> 00:42:28,861
I will!

674
00:42:28,861 --> 00:42:33,349
Everybody will die.

675
00:42:35,575 --> 00:42:38,012
There are a lot of people who have already left us.

676
00:42:38,859 --> 00:42:39,701
My dad,

677
00:42:39,701 --> 00:42:40,640
your mom,

678
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:41,607
Auntie Qin,

679
00:42:43,505 --> 00:42:45,607
but their love won't leave us.

680
00:42:47,482 --> 00:42:50,594
So, even if you're going to die, you can't push me away.

681
00:42:52,013 --> 00:42:54,741
In this world there are so many unexpected deaths.

682
00:42:55,513 --> 00:42:58,765
I don't want us to lose the chance to love each other because of fear.

683
00:43:06,263 --> 00:43:07,358
I don't want to lose you.

684
00:43:11,672 --> 00:43:13,641
Then live on.

685
00:43:16,973 --> 00:43:18,358
I will live.

686
00:43:19,380 --> 00:43:20,062
I will.

687
00:43:22,347 --> 00:43:23,231
Me too.

688
00:43:24,437 --> 00:43:27,192
Every minute and every second, I will do my best to live on.

689
00:43:47,112 --> 00:43:48,049
Dad...

690
00:44:04,548 --> 00:44:07,508
Why am I stuck here?

691
00:44:10,227 --> 00:44:13,547
Why am I not at the racing grounds,

692
00:44:15,642 --> 00:44:19,861
not in school, not at the Huo departmental store.

693
00:44:22,130 --> 00:44:24,501
Why am I here?

694
00:44:26,079 --> 00:44:30,016
Everyday it feels like I'm waiting to die.

695
00:44:38,881 --> 00:44:40,113
You're waiting to recover.

696
00:44:45,478 --> 00:44:47,941
Only now do I know

697
00:44:49,863 --> 00:44:53,488
why my dad is always angry with me.

698
00:44:54,688 --> 00:45:00,766
Why, whenever Huo Yan sees me, he will lecture me.

699
00:45:01,218 --> 00:45:02,193
Why?

700
00:45:14,982 --> 00:45:16,870
The person I used to be

701
00:45:17,806 --> 00:45:19,681
was really too wasteful.

702
00:45:23,556 --> 00:45:24,953
I always thought that

703
00:45:25,255 --> 00:45:26,225
I still had

704
00:45:27,787 --> 00:45:30,600
a lot of time ahead of me to waste.

705
00:45:32,605 --> 00:45:38,010
But now, without expecting it,

706
00:45:40,016 --> 00:45:43,778
in a moment, I suddenly seem to have

707
00:45:44,951 --> 00:45:46,254
no more time left.

708
00:45:52,599 --> 00:45:53,911
You finally realized

709
00:45:55,015 --> 00:45:58,630
one of the three biggest sins in my life is to waste.

710
00:46:00,076 --> 00:46:00,818
Don't worry,

711
00:46:01,490 --> 00:46:02,855
you've already confessed,

712
00:46:02,855 --> 00:46:04,354
Heaven will forgive you.

713
00:46:15,426 --> 00:46:17,557
He'll give me another chance, right?

714
00:46:20,771 --> 00:46:22,302
All my wastefulness in the past,

715
00:46:24,100 --> 00:46:25,538
He will fix it.

716
00:46:27,226 --> 00:46:28,023
Right?

717
00:46:37,249 --> 00:46:38,179
Definitely.

718
00:46:58,817 --> 00:47:00,203
Your son has Wilson's Disease.

719
00:47:00,484 --> 00:47:02,848
His liver is about to die from the damage,

720
00:47:03,077 --> 00:47:04,469
and we still can't find a donor.

721
00:47:04,670 --> 00:47:07,265
So his life will most likely be in danger.

722
00:47:07,945 --> 00:47:08,985
I hope you understand.

723
00:47:27,142 --> 00:47:28,726
What happened?

724
00:47:30,318 --> 00:47:32,357
One who falls sick should be around my age.

725
00:47:32,357 --> 00:47:33,605
Why is it my son?

726
00:47:36,364 --> 00:47:38,053
Why is it like this?

727
00:48:46,017 --> 00:48:47,363
Director.

728
00:49:10,056 --> 00:49:11,304
You...

729
00:49:13,525 --> 00:49:15,136
How do you feel?

730
00:49:26,435 --> 00:49:27,801
Don't be scared.

731
00:49:29,191 --> 00:49:31,688
I will get you the best doctors.

732
00:49:33,207 --> 00:49:37,215
If this hospital isn't good enough, I will have someone find another one.

733
00:49:37,489 --> 00:49:39,362
We'll definitely find the best hospital and doctors.

734
00:49:43,404 --> 00:49:44,954
Here is great.

735
00:49:46,280 --> 00:49:48,011
No matter how much money we spend,

736
00:49:48,011 --> 00:49:49,344
we have to save him.

737
00:49:50,019 --> 00:49:51,146
I know.

738
00:49:53,393 --> 00:49:54,918
What else...

739
00:49:55,616 --> 00:49:56,990
What else can I do?

740
00:49:59,423 --> 00:50:00,270
Dad...

741
00:50:00,270 --> 00:50:01,334
I'll do whatever needs to be done.

742
00:50:01,334 --> 00:50:02,267
Don't worry.

743
00:50:02,267 --> 00:50:03,612
Of course I'm worried.

744
00:50:05,237 --> 00:50:08,236
My son is sick, yet I can't do anything.

745
00:50:09,476 --> 00:50:11,642
So what if I'm Huo Zheng Hao?

746
00:50:14,392 --> 00:50:17,198
So what if I'm a force to be reckoned with in business?

747
00:50:18,134 --> 00:50:21,397
In the end, I'm still a helpless father.

748
00:50:35,820 --> 00:50:36,570
Dad,

749
00:50:41,091 --> 00:50:42,965
I read...

750
00:50:43,184 --> 00:50:45,006
mom's diary.

751
00:50:48,198 --> 00:50:49,852
She said...

752
00:50:54,270 --> 00:50:55,996
She loved you.

753
00:50:58,846 --> 00:50:59,346
So

754
00:51:01,683 --> 00:51:04,143
giving birth to me

755
00:51:05,590 --> 00:51:09,266
was mom's greatest satisfaction.

756
00:51:13,777 --> 00:51:21,059
For that reason alone, it's worth it to live on for her.

757
00:51:24,531 --> 00:51:26,500
It's me.

758
00:51:27,956 --> 00:51:33,001
I didn't take care of your mother's well being.

759
00:51:40,658 --> 00:51:45,502
I was mom's greatest satisfaction.

760
00:51:49,283 --> 00:51:50,003
But...

761
00:51:56,567 --> 00:51:59,597
my contributions to you are so bad.

762
00:52:01,020 --> 00:52:02,954
I forced you to retreat,

763
00:52:03,970 --> 00:52:05,602
gave you high blood pressure,

764
00:52:07,287 --> 00:52:09,544
embarrassed you,

765
00:52:10,649 --> 00:52:12,901
lost you money,

766
00:52:13,170 --> 00:52:14,869
that...

767
00:52:15,246 --> 00:52:17,501
...was all me.

768
00:52:20,166 --> 00:52:22,378
The one who helped you earn money,

769
00:52:23,012 --> 00:52:25,487
who gave you pride,

770
00:52:28,534 --> 00:52:31,086
I also feel so thankful for you.

771
00:52:31,876 --> 00:52:33,755
Good thing...

772
00:52:34,493 --> 00:52:36,597
you brought Huo Yan back.

773
00:52:38,804 --> 00:52:40,584
That

774
00:52:41,344 --> 00:52:43,505
was all done by him.

775
00:52:45,651 --> 00:52:49,673
It doesn't matter if there's Huo Yan,

776
00:52:50,471 --> 00:52:53,877
my expectations for you are the same.

777
00:52:55,396 --> 00:52:56,376
But you...

778
00:52:56,376 --> 00:52:59,251
I only know how to make you angry.

779
00:53:02,897 --> 00:53:04,623
I'm angry,

780
00:53:06,439 --> 00:53:09,689
but I can't truly be angry at you because...

781
00:53:13,946 --> 00:53:15,478
I know

782
00:53:17,265 --> 00:53:19,184
I let your mother down.

783
00:53:21,872 --> 00:53:24,014
And all my actions,

784
00:53:24,577 --> 00:53:25,840
without fail,

785
00:53:26,465 --> 00:53:27,997
remind you of that fact.

786
00:53:30,643 --> 00:53:31,393
Yes.

787
00:53:34,158 --> 00:53:36,180
So...

788
00:53:42,099 --> 00:53:44,654
So I don't know

789
00:53:44,654 --> 00:53:47,198
how to face you.

790
00:53:57,534 --> 00:53:59,159
Dad...

791
00:54:01,195 --> 00:54:03,411
Even though we think differently,

792
00:54:04,946 --> 00:54:09,100
your willingness to say it

793
00:54:10,955 --> 00:54:14,579
makes me very happy.

794
00:54:17,243 --> 00:54:18,868
At least,

795
00:54:21,289 --> 00:54:23,258
in your world,

796
00:54:24,678 --> 00:54:27,650
I'm not just the empty air.

797
00:54:33,557 --> 00:54:35,678
You are my son.

798
00:54:36,441 --> 00:54:38,681
Huo Yan too.

799
00:54:39,067 --> 00:54:41,178
You both are.

800
00:54:41,614 --> 00:54:43,312
I cannot lose either of you.

801
00:54:46,110 --> 00:54:48,385
I promised your mom...

802
00:54:48,701 --> 00:54:51,005
To leave the best for you.

803
00:54:58,025 --> 00:54:58,745
Dad...

804
00:55:02,205 --> 00:55:04,329
Thank you.

805
00:55:32,890 --> 00:55:33,718
Mom,

806
00:55:33,718 --> 00:55:35,912
next time I go to the hospital, I'll be back late.

807
00:55:36,173 --> 00:55:37,858
Go to bed, don't wait up for me.

808
00:55:38,141 --> 00:55:39,639
Don't worry about me.

809
00:55:40,825 --> 00:55:42,313
Is Xiao Da okay?

810
00:55:43,368 --> 00:55:45,056
I believe he'll get better.

811
00:55:45,555 --> 00:55:47,118
I believe he'll get better too.

812
00:55:51,235 --> 00:55:54,087
So you were acting mean on purpose?

813
00:55:54,514 --> 00:55:55,149
Devil,

814
00:55:55,149 --> 00:55:56,714
why are you so pitiful?

815
00:55:57,307 --> 00:55:58,104
So, all along,

816
00:55:58,104 --> 00:55:59,590
we've been wrongly accusing you?

817
00:56:00,807 --> 00:56:04,803
And I also said all of those words, cursing you to the eighteenth level of hell.

818
00:56:04,803 --> 00:56:06,163
I didn't mean it!

819
00:56:09,179 --> 00:56:09,903
Devil,

820
00:56:09,903 --> 00:56:12,224
your love for Jia Di is really too great!

821
00:56:12,721 --> 00:56:14,471
I'm really touched.

822
00:56:14,903 --> 00:56:16,106
You're too exaggerated.

823
00:56:22,025 --> 00:56:25,313
Could you please not tell Bo Zi and the rest?

824
00:56:25,700 --> 00:56:26,540
Why?

825
00:56:26,540 --> 00:56:28,169
Bo Zi said that he wanted to cut all ties with you.

826
00:56:28,169 --> 00:56:29,343
I'm going to go tell him right now.

827
00:56:30,204 --> 00:56:33,076
I don't want to let this affect them.

828
00:56:34,996 --> 00:56:39,386
I don't know if it's right to say this, but I feel since there's a problem,

829
00:56:39,386 --> 00:56:40,825
why don't you explain it clearly to everyone?

830
00:56:51,291 --> 00:56:54,105
The Devil just left like that. He really isn't a good friend.

